@startuml
title LISA LOXLAY - Service Request Sequence

actor "Customer / Branch User" as Customer
participant "LISA Portal" as Portal
participant "LISA Ticket Core" as Lisa
participant "SLA Engine" as SLA
participant "Service Desk" as Desk
participant "Field Engineer" as Engineer
participant "Asset & Inventory" as Inventory
participant "Notification Gateway" as Notify

Customer -> Portal: Submit incident / service request
Portal -> Lisa: Create LISA ticket
Lisa -> SLA: Calculate priority and SLA target
SLA --> Lisa: Priority, response time, resolution time
Lisa -> Notify: Send ticket confirmation
Notify --> Customer: SMS / email / app notification

Lisa -> Desk: Queue new ticket
Desk -> Lisa: Review customer, contract, asset

alt Remote support possible
  Desk -> Customer: Contact and troubleshoot
  Desk -> Lisa: Record remote resolution
else Onsite support required
  Desk -> Engineer: Assign onsite job
  Engineer -> Lisa: Accept job
  Engineer -> Inventory: Check spare part

  alt Spare part available
    Inventory --> Engineer: Reserve spare part
  else Spare part unavailable
    Inventory --> Lisa: Backorder required
    Lisa -> Notify: Notify delay and ETA
    Notify --> Customer: Waiting for spare part
  end

  Engineer -> Customer: Visit site and repair
  Engineer -> Lisa: Submit service report
end

Lisa -> SLA: Validate SLA result
SLA --> Lisa: Met / breached
Lisa -> Customer: Request confirmation
Customer --> Lisa: Confirm service completion
Lisa -> Notify: Send satisfaction survey

@enduml
